# How to make a big image on the website from vague to clear, but not show in a slow way?

The markdown will tell you how to solve it in a `vue-project`.


First, you should know `antimoderate` plugin.[github](https://github.com/whackashoe/antimoderate)

Second, you may able to know how to make a local picture to a smaller size one and make it to be 'base-64'.
[smaller your image](https://jingyan.baidu.com/article/066074d63d1f2cc3c21cb0c4.html)
[online-base64](https://www.css-js.com/tools/base64.html)

Finally, you may take my follow.

page.vue
```

 <template>
  <div class="page">
    <img src="../../static/com_1.jpg" height="71" width="50" id="picture" style="width:200px; height:200px;" :data-antimoderate-idata="com_1">
  </div>
  </template>

  <script>
  import AntiModerate from 'antimoderate'
  import imgsBase64 from './img_base64.js'
    export default {
      data() {
        return {
          com_1: imgsBase64.com_1
        }
      },
      methods: {
      },
      mounted () {
        var img = document.getElementById('picture');
        AntiModerate.process(img, img.getAttribute("data-antimoderate-idata"))
      }
    }
  </script>

```

img_base64.js

```
export default {
  com_1: "data:image/jpeg;base64,"
}
```
